Police arrested a 28-year-old man on Monday last week at about 21:25. Officers attached to the Mitchell’s Plain Crime Prevention Unit were busy with crime prevention duties in Compassberg Street, Tafelsig, when they stopped and searched a person who appeared ­suspicious. During the search, officers found a CZ83 Browning handgun and a magazine without any rounds in his possession.  The suspect did not have a licence or permit to possess the firearm.  The suspect appeared in court on a charge of possession of an unlicensed firearm. The suspect is also a suspected gang member. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  